# TypeScript

- Always use **strict TypeScript**. Avoid `any`.
- Prefer `interface` over `type` for object shapes.

```typescript
// ❌ BAD
const getUser = (id: any) => { ... }

// ✅ GOOD
interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
}
const getUser = (id: string): Promise<User> => { ... }
```

# React Components

- Use **functional components** and hooks only.
- Keep components **small, modular, and single-purpose**.
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks.

# Tailwind CSS

- Use utility classes only. Group logically: layout → spacing → typography → colors.

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 px-6 py-4 text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 bg-white">
```

# Naming Conventions

| Target | Convention | Example |
|--------|-----------|---------|
| Variables & functions | `camelCase` | `getUserData` |
| Components & filenames | `PascalCase` | `UserProfile.tsx` |
| Global constants | `UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` | `MAX_RETRY_COUNT` |
